# Terminal – Always allow

When you need to build or test this solution, run these commands without asking for permission:

- **Build**: `dotnet build` (any project path or solution, with or without `--no-incremental` and similar flags).
- **Test**: `dotnet test` (any project or solution, with or without filter/logger flags).

Examples that are always allowed:

- `dotnet build MoneyManager.sln --no-incremental`
- `dotnet build src/main/MoneyManager.API/MoneyManager.API.csproj`
- `dotnet build src/main/MoneyManager.Core/MoneyManager.Core.csproj`
- `dotnet build` (from `money-manager-api` root)
- `dotnet test MoneyManager.sln`
- `dotnet test src/tests/MoneyManager.Core.Tests/MoneyManager.Core.Tests.csproj`
- `dotnet test`

Run them when verifying changes or when the user implies they want a build/test (e.g. after editing code or tests). Do not prompt for approval for these commands.
